##################################
## Personal Suffixes (Pronouns) ##
##################################

# Our analysis treats pronouns as suffixes to the
# verb rather than particles, in contrast to the
# analyses of Suttles, Gerdts and others. Personal
# suffixes attach after transitive and past tense
# affixes, but before future tense. Halkomelem distinguishes
# between personal suffixes in the main clause and
# in the subordinate clause. The current grammar permits
# either type, a shortcoming that will be addressed
# in later labs.

# There is no personal suffix for the 3rd person 
# singular. 3rd person (sg or pl) is instead indicated 
# by the absence of the other suffixes. The suffix
# ʔeɬtən has been kept in the paradigm for now, but
# its distribution is actually a bit freer than the
# other suffixes and may require reanalysis in the
# future.

# Main clause personal suffixes:

#       sg           pl
# 1     -cən  1SUBJ  -ct     1PSUBJ
# 2     -tʃxᵂ 1SUBJ  -cep    2PSUBJ
# 3     --           -ʔeɬtən 3PSUBJ

# Subordinate clause personal suffixes:

#       sg              pl
# 1     -en   1SUBSUBJ  -ət  1PSUBSUBJ
# 2     -əxᵂ  2SUBSUBJ  -ep  2PSUBSUBJ
# 3     -əs   3SUBSUBJ  -əs  3SUBSUBJ


